title: COVID-19 In Japan
description: Welcome to our new blog, In this blog, we will take a deeper look into the COVID-19 situation in Japan and explore its effect on different locations of Japan. We hope you enjoy reading what we have to say and lets get started!
contents:
Introduction
Covid-19 is a disease caused by a form of coronavirus that can cause respiratory infections that range from the common cold to more serious diseases.With its strong trasnmissiblity among public, it is true indeed to say that the COVID-19 pandemic has presented an unprecedent challenge to public health across the globe. As the number of cases confirmed with the virus continue to climb around the world, many countries has produced vacination in attempt to stop the pandemic. Thus, to better understand the virus and its characteristic, we will be examining the the impact COVID-19 pandemic in this blog, by first looking the COVID-19 positive rate and death rate in Post-1. Later followed by analysis on recovery rate, vacinnation rate in post 2.
Data description
To conduct our exploration of the impact of COVID in japan, we will be using multiple datasets (owid-covid-data.csv, prefectures.csv, prefecture.csv) for our analysis. 2 of the datasets (prefectures.csv, prefecture.csv) were sourced from Toyo Keizai Online “Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) Situation Report in Japan” with its orginal data provided by the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare in Japan. The owid-covid-data.csv dataset are provided by our world in data with its orginal data sourced from the COVID-19 Data Repository by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) at Johns Hopkins University (JHU). No data wrangling and tidying was conducted as the datasets have already been tided when sourced.
